<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF107-974-590  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 974 590.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC-Computing  Jan 1990 v3 n1 p197(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Mike Falkner on databases. (Pro tips.)andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Falkner, Mike.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Product:   Q and A (Data base management system) (usage).andO;Topic:     Data base management systemsSoftware PackagesTutorialUser Assistance.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Mike Falkner on DatabasesandM;Zip codes speed mail delivery, and they can also save you time and keystrokeswhen you create mailing lists.andP;  By using a lookup function, you can use zipcodes to search a database table and automatically fill in the otherinformation your records require.andP;  I use Symantec's Qandamp;A in this example, butany database manager with a lookup function (though it may be calledsomething else) can do the same.andM;Say you want to create a database to store information about local clients.andO;You live in a metropolitan area with many suburbs near the border of twostates, so you can't just duplicate city, state, and area code informationfrom record to record.andP;  In most cases, however, these fields will be the samefor a given zip code.andM;Create a database called ZIPS with fields for zip code, city, state, and areacode.andP;  Using the Customize a File option, make zip code a unique search fieldto speed up searches and to catch typing mistakes.andP;  Using information foundin your local phone book or in your client records, enter the data for ZIPSso that each zip code record is accompanied by the corresponding city, state,and area code.andM;Now create a second database with fields for name, two address lines, city,state, zip, area code, phone number, and any other data you may need.andP;  Whenyou create the entry form, place the zip code before city, state, and areacode.andP;  Select Program Form and add the following statements to the fieldsbefore the colon:andM;Zip code : #1 City : @XLOOKUP(&quot;ZIPS&quot;,#1,&quot;Zip code&quot;,&quot;City&quot;) State :@XLOOKUP(&quot;ZIPS&quot;,#1,&quot;Zip code&quot;,&quot;State&quot;) Area code: @XLOOKUP(&quot;ZIPS&quot;, #1,&quot;Zipcode&quot;,&quot;Area Code&quot;)andM;Now, when you're entering information into the form and you enter the zipcode, Qandamp;A's @XLOOKUP command automatically brings the city, state, and areacode into the form.andP;  If the zip code you enter is not valid or theinformation the lookup function enters for the rest of the form is incorrect,Qandamp;A lets you make changes.andP;  Even with a few manual corrections, you'll stillsave a lot of time.andM;Mike Falkner is an independent microcomputer consultant and a PC coordinatorfor a Sacramento, California, manufacturer.andO;</TEXT></DOC>